column1: Time-series data for inorganic carbon chemistry (DIC, ALK, d13C-DIC) from discrete bottle
samples from surface seawater. Each row designates the average of one or two bottles
from a specific depth and time and date. Data have been screened to remove contaminated
Carbon measurements include total dissolved inorganic carbon (DIC), the reduced isotope
ratio 13C/12C of DIC (d13C-DIC), and alkalinity (ALK). Salinity measurements are based on
bottle seawater. Temperature measured with CTD hydrocast.
